@jameslamb Just awesome! I don't think that a lot of projects can say that they replicate all CRAN checks at their CI, but we are very close to this!

Please take a look at some my comments below.

After merging this PR I'll try to make this test be either skipped or successful as I stated in https://github.com/microsoft/LightGBM/pull/3439#issuecomment-706621807.

I've made a phosphor/lumino message processing compatibility implementation in a package like this. Any input on the implementation itself? Any suggestions for where to best put it in the migration guide?

```ts
class MyWidget extends DOMWidgetView {

  _processLuminoMessage(msg: Message, _super: (msg: Message) => void): void {
    _super.call(this, msg);
    switch (msg.type) {
    case 'after-attach':
      // Auto-sizing should be updated when attached to DOM:
      this.onChange();
      break;
    }
  }

  processPhosphorMessage(msg: Message): void {
    this._processLuminoMessage(msg, (DOMWidgetView as any).processPhosphorMessage);
  }

  processLuminoMessage(msg: Message): void {
    this._processLuminoMessage(msg, (DOMWidgetView as any).processLuminoMessage);
  }
}
```

@jameslamb 
Awesome work!
Thanks a lot for digging deep in sklearn internals and finding way not to make a parent aware of its children. I left some comments for your consideration.

@hegusung Thanks for this work! This was a significant gap in boofuzz.

After this PR, it wouldn't be much work to integrate the two procmon scripts, since the Simple debugger will work with both Windows and Unix.

Thanks @SR4ven for the review!

@nikitavemuri the code looks good; could you please update the relevant places in the serve docs to reflect this change (`doc/source/serve/*` and `python/ray/serve/examples/*`)? Concretely:

- Add a section about isolating Serve using namespaces to the `Deploying Ray Serve` section.
- Remove the `namespace` arg from everywhere else where it isn't directly relevant and may cause confusion.

@hoonhan Thanks a lot for the contribution!

Your proposal makes sense. One issue is that currently we are trying to move off from the `ToTensor` idiom because it does too many things (converts the image to tensor and rescales the values). We are currently moving towards allowing the user to choose whether the images should remain on their original uint8 space as this can have memory and performance benefits. We also work on adopting meta-data-rich tensors that would give to the user the colour space of the image, the size and other useful info. This is part of our Transforms V2 initiative which is in progress. Due to this, I would rather to not make any further expansions to the specific methods until the new API is finalised. This will help the faster adoption of the next idioms.

@pmeier @vfdev-5 This is useful feedback, perhaps we should consider it as an expansion on the new API. WDYT?

@satsuki-chan 

this is a valiant effort but it seems to rely too much on reformatting the HTML and logging try excepts.  

I laid out some simple fixes that should let you streamline the code down and avoid errors that might be caused by bad entries in the future.
